%I A397334 #64 Jul 09 2026 11:31:19
%S A397334 3,2,1,18,98,1229536,50336940
%N A397334 Least m such that the chain u_0 = m, u_{k+1} = pi(u_k+prime(u_k)), where u_k + prime(u_k) is prime, has length n.
%e A397334 3 + prime(3) = 3 + 5 = 8 = 2^3. So a(0) = 3.
%e A397334 2 + prime(2) = 2 + 3 = 5 = prime(3), and 3 + prime(3) = 3 + 5 = 8 = 2^3. So a(1) = 2.
%e A397334 1 + prime(1) = 1 + 2 = 3 = prime(2), 2 + prime(2) = 2 + 3 = 5 = prime(3), and 3 + prime(3) = 3 + 5 = 8 = 2^3. So a(2) = 1.
%e A397334 18 + prime(18) = 18 + 61 = 79 = prime(22), 22 + prime(22) = 22 + 79 = 101 = prime(26), 26 + prime(26) = 26 + 101 = 127 = prime(31), and 31 + prime(31) = 31 + 127 = 158 = 2 * 79. So a(3) = 18.
%e A397334 98 + prime(98) = 98 + 521 = 619 = prime(114), 114 + prime(114) = 114 + 619 = 733 = prime(130), 130 + prime(130) = 130 + 733 = 863 = prime(150), 150 + prime(150) = 150 + 863 = 1013 = prime(170), and 170 + prime(170) = 170 + 1013 = 1183 = 7 * 13^2. So a(4) = 98.
%e A397334 And no lesser numbers have this property.
%o A397334 (PARI) f(n) = my(nb=0, k); while (isprime(k=n + prime(n)), nb++; n = primepi(k)); nb;
%o A397334 a(n) = my(k=1); while(f(k) != n , k++); k; \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jul 09 2026
%Y A397334 Cf. A000040, A061067, A061068, A064402.
